The paper deals with the recovery of images from non-uniform Fourier samples, which is a problem commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and computer vision (cs.CV) communities. The use of a convex matrix completion algorithm also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of the algorithm to MRI data, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
